'''Adam S. Miller''', an American writer of religious criticism and interpretation and also of contemporary [[Church of Jesus Christ of Latter-day Saints|Latter-day Saint]] [[lay theologian|lay theology]], is a professor of philosophy at [[Collin College]] in McKinney, Texas, where he directs the college's honors program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://claremontmormonstudies.org/event/lecture-by-dr-adam-miller-professor-of-philosophy-collin-college-title-tba/|title=Lecture by Dr. Adam Miller, Professor of Philosophy, Collin College (2014-09-19)|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://religionnews.com/2015/03/10/mormon-author-says-grace-not-gods-backup-plan/|title=Mormon author says "grace is not God’s backup plan"|first=Jana|last=Riess|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.irishcentral.com/news/irishvoice/do-we-really-care-if-the-us-founding-fathers-were-anti-catholic|title=Do we really care if the US Founding Fathers were anti-Catholic?|date=28 January 2015|publisher=}}</ref>

Miller has offered a fresh interpretation of such things as Christ's atonement,<ref>{{cite book|url = https://books.google.com/books?id=yU1uBAAAQBAJ&pg=PA371&dq=%22Adam+Miller%22+mormon&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwiWyNyymqfPAhWQuB4KHdnwBYU4ChC7BQg9MAY#v=onepage&q=%22Adam%20Miller%22%20mormon&f=false| title = Wrestling the Angel: The Foundations of Mormon Thought: Cosmos, God, Humanity| author = [[Terryl L. Givens]]| publisher = [[Oxford University Press]]|year =  2014}}</ref> the appropriate relationship of scholarship with faith,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sltrib.com/lifestyle/faith/1872447-155/byu-prof-fears-mormon-scholars-are|title=BYU prof fears Mormon scholars are giving in to secularism|first=Peggy Fletcher Stack  The Salt Lake|last=Tribune|publisher=}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.deseretnews.com/article/705302268/A-Mormon-theology-manifesto.html?pg=all|title=A Mormon theology manifesto|first=Michael De|last=Groote|date=9 May 2009|publisher=}}</ref> and the nature of Latter-day Saint "testimony".<ref>http://aporia.byu.edu/pdfs/struk-the_hermeneutics_of_testimony.pdf</ref> Miller co-founded Salt Press, a publisher of Mormon studies sold to BYU's [[Maxwell Institute]],<ref>{{cite web|url=http://mi.byu.edu/salt-press/|title=Salt Press titles coming to the Maxwell Institute|publisher=}}</ref> and also founded and serves as co-director of the annual colloquia, the Mormon Theology Seminar.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://religionnews.com/2014/10/17/know-church-true-mormon-muddles/|title="I know the Church is true," and other Mormon muddles|first=Jana|last=Riess|publisher=}}</ref>

